history.text: Hello!  What movie do you want to talk about?
The Wold of Wall Street is the one I got
I've been interested in the Wolf of Wall Street for a while.  What kind of movie is it?
It's a comedy about the life of Jordan Belfort
Comedies are pretty good.  What did Jordan Belfort do?
He was a stockbroker in New York city and basically became a millionaire by selling penny stocks
That sounds pretty interesting for a comedy.  Is the movie getting good reviews?

It's got rotten tomatoes score of 78% and metacritic score of 75/100 but I would definitely recommend
 it
Those are some solid scores.  Do you know who directed it?
Martin Scorsese did
I know he's directed some pretty good stuff in the past.  Have you seen the Wolf of Wall Street?
Yes i have
Was it popular when it came out?
Oh yeah! My friends and I all went to watch it
That's awesome haha.  Do you know who all acted in it?
Leonardo DiCaprio, Jonah Hill, Margot Robbie...
That's a pretty star-studded list.  I know that DiCaprio's been in a lot of good movies.  Do you know if the Wolf of Wall Street win any awards or anything like that?
I think DiCaprio won the golden globe award for best actor
It's not an Oscar, but at least it counts!  Is the Wolf of Wall Street more of an adult movie, or is it a family sort of thing?
Definitely an adult movie
I kinda figured that with the subject matter.  Is it a longer movie?
yeah about 3 hours
Wow; that's pretty long.  Does it just go through how Jordan Belfort got rich off of selling penny stocks?
It also deals with his personal life and how he got married and ended up in jail later on
I can see why it would end up being 3 hours then.  Do you know why he ended up in jail towards the end?
He was convicted for fraud
That seems like it could make for a fun movie, then.  Is DiCaprio the one playing Jordan Belfort?
Yeah, he is
Okay then; I'll have to check it out.  Thanks for telling me about it!

uid1response.feedback: The movie seemed interesting, and the other user gave me a good description of what it was about.  The conversation went fairly well, and the instructions were clear.  Thanks!
